{
  "_comment": "Icon registry for SEEngine. Each entry maps a canonical concept to a tier (folder), an Iconify name (for sync_icons.py to fetch), and aliases (alternate user-typed labels). The resolver uses this in: exact key -> alias -> semantic fallback -> None (text-only).",
  "_tiers": ["vendor", "saas", "tech", "cloud", "generic"],
  "_iconify_api": "https://api.iconify.design/{iconify}.svg",
  "_format": "svg",
  "_aws_note": "Cloud service icons live under tier='cloud'. Canonical keys are cloud-prefixed (aws_ec2, azure_blob, gcp_gke) to avoid collisions; aliases let users type the bare service name (ec2, s3). AWS services pulled from logos: and simple-icons: on Iconify. Azure/GCP service-level icons need Microsoft's / Google's official SVG kits dropped into assets/icons/cloud/ manually — Iconify only carries the master Azure/GCP logos.",

